:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;eloquent_imagery_image&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;path&quot;:&quot;articles\/05PkcvCkhgqwVpN4bmSg2sm-2.png&quot;,&quot;altText&quot;:&quot;Microsoft Flight Simulator&#039;s control schemes&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;(Image: Microsoft)&quot;}},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;paragraph&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;One would think that a game entitled Microsoft Flight Simulator would push virtual pilots toward purchasing a flight stick, but that is not the case. Though the game is compatible with flight sticks, the game is also designed with &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;gamepads&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/www.pcmag.com\/how-to\/how-to-choose-the-right-game-controller-for-your-pc&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:null}}]},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot; and &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;mouse&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/www.pcmag.com\/picks\/the-best-gaming-mice&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:null}}]},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;-and-&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;keyboard&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/www.pcmag.com\/picks\/the-best-gaming-keyboards&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:null}}]},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot; setups in mind. In fact, it auto-detects the controllers connected to your PC, and asks you to select a preferred control setup. Developer Asobo Studio and publisher Xbox Game Studios want you to be as comfortable as possible behind the yoke.&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;paragraph&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Confession time. Despite being a die-hard PC gamer in recent years, most of my gaming life has been lived as a console pleb. So, my first instinct was to grab the ol&#039; Xbox gamepad. To my surprise, the console controller worked shockingly well. I had precise, tight controller over the yoke, and released brakes and lowered landing gear with just a button press or two. That said, the &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Thrustmaster TCA Officer Pack Airbus Edition&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;href&quot;:&quot;http:\/\/www.thrustmaster.com\/en_US\/products\/tca-officer-pack-airbus-edition&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:null}}]},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot; may be the ultimate Flight Simulator control scheme, one that is tempting me to kick the Xbox controller to the curb.&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;horizontal_rule&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;level&quot;:2},&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;It&#039;s a Casual-Friendly Sim&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;eloquent_imagery_image&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;path&quot;:&quot;articles\/05PkcvCkhgqwVpN4bmSg2sm-4.jpg&quot;,&quot;altText&quot;:&quot;Microsoft Flight Simulator&#039;s Cockpit&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;(Image: Microsoft)&quot;}},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;paragraph&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;The idea of hyper-realistic airplane controls in a video game is enough to turn off many potential players. After all, a cockpit is chock full of bewildering knobs, gauges, and switches. Thankfully, Microsoft Flight Simulator lets you scale the control level from fully manual controls to fully assisted controls, with highlighted instrument guidance. &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;paragraph&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Eight tutorial missions teach everything you need to know about flight, from reading the instrument console to learning how to take off and land. Fortunately, this is executed via an extremely chatty, user-selected co-pilot who explains what things are and how they work. You just may walk away from Microsoft Flight Simulator with a new appreciation for the pilot profession.&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;horizontal_rule&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;heading&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;level&quot;:2},&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;It Has Relatively Low System Requirements, But Big Customization&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;}]},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;eloquent_imagery_image&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;path&quot;:&quot;articles\/05PkcvCkhgqwVpN4bmSg2sm-3.png&quot;,&quot;altText&quot;:&quot;Microsoft Flight Simulator&#039;s system specs&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;(Image: Microsoft)&quot;}},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;paragraph&quot;,&quot;content&quot;:[{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Flight Simulator is a gorgeous game when running on high-end hardware, but Microsoft made certain that many PC gamers could experience the thrills of manned flight. All you need to initiate takeoff is a PC that has at least an AMD Ryzen 3 1200 or Intel Core i5-4460 CPU, AMD Radeon RX 570 or Nvidia GeForce GTX 770 GPU, 8GB of RAM, 150GB of storage, and the &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Windows 10&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/www.pcmag.com\/reviews\/microsoft-windows-10&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:null}}]},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot; operating system. (Read &quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;},{&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Can Your PC Run Microsoft Flight Simulator?&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;text&quot;,&quot;marks&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;link&quot;,&quot;attrs&quot;:{&q